hondo717: Now this is an interesting hand in bidding tactics. First of all some people would bid 1@H or 2@H with my hand over 1@D. And indeed, had terry not opened, I would have opened 2 hearts. However, because all my points are outside of hearts, I chose not to bid my hearts, as they were long but not too strong. But many would choose to bid 1@H or 2@H, and that would be ok. Now, once kia bids hearts, I have a clear 4@H bid, as I know we have an 11 card fit and, as you see we make 4 hearts. On the other hand, I was afraid that by bidding 4@H I might push them into 5@D, which could easily make.|
