hondo717: This is one hand where there is a big difference between 2 over 1 system and sayc. In sayc, which is what we are bidding, kia's 2@H bid only promises 10 points. If I had a minimum hand with hearts, I would only bid 3@H, and kia would bid 4 with an opener. However, since I have 19 points, I know we should be in game, so I bid 4@H and then kia can now think about slam, since he has a solid opener, and knows we have a fit in 2 suits. Next, I suggest 4NT, on the off chance we are missing 2 key cards. BTW, although we made 7, that was only because the spade finesse worked. you should only bid grands that are 75% or more, and this is only 50%.|
