hondo717: I think RKC is a terrific convention. I rarely cue bid any more. Further, there is one wrinkle to cue bidding in this auction that I already mentioned. Technically, kia could cue bid the ace of spades. But, that is an ambiguous bid, because I might interpret that as simply preferring spades over hearts. So kia cannot cue bid 4@S on that particular auction. Generally speaking, 4NT is good enough in looking for slam. The only time cue bidding is better is on distributional hands where there is shortness. I suggest you stick to Blackwood for the most part. cue bidding often gets you into trouble.|
